column84: What are your thoughts on 3D wiggle stereoscopy?
I found this technique very creative technique to simulate depth perception by alternating between two images.
I find this effect pretty interesting and also think, for it to be better perceived, the images must have exactly the same dimensions. I really hope my comment is useful to the author.

3D Wiggle Stereoscopy creates a depth illusion by rapidly switching between two slightly different images. This mimics human vision, making objects appear three-dimensional without special glasses. It’s popular in GIFs and photography but can feel jittery.
It’s good to look at 2d images with different 3D illusion effect
It creates a 3D effect by quickly switching between two images, but can be hard to focus on.
